        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We wish to use band~7 and the C34-6 configuration of the array. For G31.41+0.31 this implies and angular resolution of 0."2 (obtained with the OST simulator). We stress that the maximum extent of the jet is less than the HMC diameter of 2", and thus less than the maximum angular scale that can be imaged with the requested configuration (2."5). The SiO(8-7) line will be covered with a 469~MHz baseband allowing for 0.42 km/s resolution, while other basebands will be suitably placed to cover the H13CO+(4-3), SO10(11)-10(10), SO2 23(3,21)-23(2,22), and CH3CN 19-18 transitions. The 3-sigma level of the SiO(8-7) line measured in the 0."8 beam of the SMA is 5 K, and this allows detection of the line wings, important to trace the high-velocity gas in the jet. Note that this value is a lower limit to the brightness temperature that will be measured in the ALMA 0."2 beam. We wish to detect the SiO wing emission with a S/N=10 and therefore require a 1-sigma RMS of 0.5 K (1.97 mJy). According to the OT, this requires a total observing time of 3.4 hours, assuming 0.8 km/s resolution sufficient to resolve lines that in G31.41+0.31 are known to be as broad as 8 km/s (see e.g. Beltran et al. 2005).</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
